==English==
===Etymology===
*from Pangasinan word ''pangasinan'', "place of salt" or "place of salt-production"; from Pangasinan root word ''asin'', "salt"
===Pronunciation===
*pang-guh-see-nan
===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Pangasinan'''
# a [[province]] of the [[Philippines]] along the Lingayen Gulf in the island of [[Luzon]]
# a [[language]] of the [[Malayo-Polynesian]] branch of the [[Austronesian]] family of languages spoken in the [[Philippines]], which is the primary language in the province or region of [[Pangasinan]]
# a [[region]] of the Philippines along the Lingayen Gulf in the island of Luzon which is known for its [[salt]]-production industry
# a [[region]] of the [[Philippines]] along the Lingayen Gulf in the island of [[Luzon]] with its distinct [[Pangasinan language]] and culture
# a [[nation]] identified with the region of [[Pangasinan]] and with the [[Pangasinan language]] and culture
# a [[people]] identified with the region, province or nation of [[Pangasinan]] or with the [[Pangasinan language]] and culture
# a [[native speaker]] of the [[Pangasinan language]]
# a [[resident]] or [[inhabitant]] of the province, region or nation of [[Pangasinan]]
# a [[Filipino]] or [[ethnic group]] predominantly of the [[Malay]] race identified with the [[Philippines]] or [[Filipino nation]]
# a ceramic jar or container for storage of [[salt]] or salted products
===Adjective===
'''Pangasinan'''
# Pangasinan language; of or pertaining to the Pangasinan language
# Of or pertaining to the Pangasinan people
# Of or pertaining to the Pangasinan province, region or nation
# Of or pertaining to the process of salt-production and storage of salt or salted products
# Of or pertaining to the Pangasinan coastal region known for its salt-production industry

